cordings\' Richard Russell. In an interview with Rolling Stone conducted during Coachella, the Blur frontman revealed that he recently wrapped up his new \"folk soul\" album and plans to go on tour behind the LP, playing a variety of tunes spanning his lengthy career from Blur to the Gorillaz to <span>the Good, the Bad and the Queen</span>. Russell produced and contributed to the rhythm section of the solo album and worked with Albarn on the Bobby Womack album. There was also a hint that a new Blur LP might also be a possibility, with Albarn saying, \"We\'ve got a couple of occasions when we\'re stuck in the middle','http://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2013/05/damon-albarn-solo-album-in-the-works-new-blur-lp-p.html','2013-05-28T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('5e6827063d886bdc7476f91dc74c1584','AR2A6UJ1187FB4BF5C','Damon Albarn on Blur, His First Ever Solo Album and Why He Doesn\'t Hate Oasis Anymore','festival gigs in Europe this summer, is a definite possibility. \"We\'ve got a couple of occasions when we\'re stuck in the middle of nowhere,\" he says. \"So we might make the record in a week. If we can, it would be nice.\" What drives you to take on all these different projects? There\'s Blur; Gorillaz; <span>the Good, the Bad and the Queen</span>; two operas; and way more. I get bored extremely easily. Blur was definitely my Nineties, Gorillaz was my 2000s, and then I\'ve done a lot of different stuff this decade. How connected do you feel to songs you wrote, at this point, decades ago? I enjoy playing them. A lot of the songs were quite','http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/q-a-damon-albarn-on-the-future-of-blur-his-first-ever-solo-album-and-why-he-doesnt-hate-oasis-anymore-20130528','2013-05-28T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('e74ead4df9f3715824b60ab330a6