ews/list-hub/stand-alone-soundtracks/','2013-02-20T00:00:00','2013-02-19T21:27:19');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('c2e2bfe7eda2c88665ae14291cb23069','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Video: The  Weeknd – “Twenty Eight”','have some topless women on your computer screen for about four minutes? No? Do you promise? Okay then, press play on the Weeknd\'s \"Twenty Eight\" video, directed by rising star Nabil. It\'s a gorgeous video - watch Abel Tesfaye hit up a foreign talk show, visit a really creepy and exclusive <span>Paris, Texas</span>-esque strip club, deal with his crippling postmodern ennui, and reminisce about a ghostly ex, all to the soundtrack of one of our favorite songs from his trilogy of mixtapes. Check it out. Read more articles like \"Video: The Weeknd - \"Twenty Eight\"\" on Pretty Much Amazing.Tags: The Weeknd Video: The Weeknd','http://prettymuchamazing.com/videos/twenty-eight','2013-02-13T00:00:00','2013-02-13T19:00:57');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('69cf36154a11f072a8fa994b88fa3497','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','FT:Jean Rollin The Living Dead Girl R0 3 Disc, Jean Luc-Godard Hail Mary R4 & more','La Femme Publique Husbands History on My Arms The State I Am In Une Femme Mariee (A Married Woman) The Important Thing is To Love REC Criterion wants : Life During Wartime Black Moon Tiny Furniture The Hit Red Desert Vivre sa vie World on a Wire Belle de Jour Cul-de-sac Revanche <span>Paris, Texas</span> Repulsion High & Low Che Insignificanse Carlos El Norte Il Generale della Rovere Europa Kes White Material White Dog Le Doulos Andrzej Wajda - Three War Films WR: Mysteries of the Organism Death of a Cyclist Under the Volcano Cronos The Magician Merry Christmas Mr. Lawrence Homicide Sawdust and Tinsel Mishima: A','http://forum.dvdtalk.com/dvd-exchange/608680-ft-jean-rollin-living-dead-girl-r0-3-disc-jean-luc-godard-hail-mary-r4-more.html','2013-02-13T00:00:00','2013-02-13T03:36:18');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('1d9e8272643f18093b7f8fb562036471','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','INTERVIEW: The Dark Flowers','\'Clean Break\' starts off as ambient soundscape, built on natural harmonics and layered vocals, before resolving into a graceful album centrepoint, laced with gothic chromatics. While Statham cites Brian Eno, Bruce Langhorne and Bon Iver as sonic touchstones, there are also shades, fittingly, of Ry Cooder\'s <span>Paris, Texas</span> theme in the electronic swells overlaid with sharply plucked guitar and banjo. We talked to Statham, Kerr, Catherine and Allison about the recording of the album and how Shephard\'s text figures in it. What was it about Motel Chronicles that was so captivating? Paul Statham: Short pieces of beautiful prose that seemed to say or infer a whole different world you could tap into... the visual equivalent of my first impression of Brian Eno\'s classic album Another Green World. Were you aware of Sam Shephard before reading the book? PS: Yes, <span>Paris, Texas</span>, a great film, for which Sam Shepard wrote the screen play, was also coincidentally a big influence with endless train tracks, neon-lit motels and beautiful characters. Jim Kerr: Yes, I had read some of his writing and also seen some of the film projects that he had been involved in. Catherine AD: I was aware of him mostly from <span>Paris, Texas</span>, which I adore, and I\'d had an unread copy of Motel Chronicles on my bookshelf for a few years. It was probably an advantage to not be that familiar with his work as it takes it away from the idea of a musical literary adaptation, which I\'d done before, and more into the realm of capturing the essence of a particular world that he creates in his writing. It\'s actually quite refreshing as someone who usually writes in total isolation to have these fixed and finite parameters for a change. Dot Allison: Only as an actor. Do you know if he\'s heard any of the album? PS: Ah, well I tried to contact him','http://thequietus.com/articles/11156-the-dark-flowers-jim-kerr-catherine-ad-dot-allison-paul-statham-interview','2013-01-24T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('7bbc7e5cf874d4b3a5918cc9c6a969a8','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','A Year in Music: Matthew Schnipper','music but get tired of listening. I watch a lot of movies, and as someone who by nature is obsessed with things that are part of \"the conversation,\" lately I\'ve been trying to branch out both internationally and in time, catching up on a lot of left field classics. A month or so ago I finally watched <span>Paris, Texas</span>, something I\'d been meaning to do for some time. I liked it a lot, and after watching, as I usually do, went online to read the New York Times review. It was written by Vincent Canby, who was a critic there for 35 years. I\'ve become familiar with his slightly cranky taste, and while he was generally praiseworthy of <span>Paris, Texas</span>, he took it to task--not unfairly--for wrapping up way too neatly a film whose powers lie in its imprecision. Having read a lot of his reviews, I\'ve both admired and been totally annoyed by how difficult it was to impress him and, knowing he died, wondered if maybe that reputation got a note in his obituary. It did, with Janet Maslin poking light fun at his blasé attitude towards E.T. She also made good case for his high standards, quoting from a piece he wrote about criticism in 1979. Covering the New York Film Festival at Lincoln Center and wrestling with a memory of watching','http://www.thefader.com/2012/12/19/a-year-in-music-matthew-schnipper-2/','2012-12-19T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id