but the vocals are sometimes a little too geeky for my taste...','http://www.lostatsea.net/LAS/archives/reviews/records/paristexas_brazilliant.jpg','http://www.lostatsea.net/review.phtml?id=52592604241f7ddc609c8a','2010-02-19T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - Like You Like an Arsonist (from Delusions of Adequacy)','Like You Like an Arsonist','Paris, Texas\'s Like You Like an Arsonist is the sound of a collision between The Alkaline Trio\'s demented glee and a grunge-rock band, which is the magic formula for the movement we now call garage rock (it used to be called rock\'n\'roll). The music isn\'t exactly angry or happy: chunky, forceful riffs lay out a sound that could best be described as rebellious. The band is more comparable to an angrier Jet, or a less caustic Yeah Yeah Yeahs, or a more polished Hives...','http://www.adequacy.net/wp-content/uploads/images/covers/4307-Cover.jpg','http://www.adequacy.net/2004/06/paris-texas-like-you-like-an-arsonist/','2009-07-21T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - Brazilliant! EP (from Delusions of Adequacy)','Brazilliant! EP','Just when I had pretty much given up on Paris, Texas, they release this, their newest EP and their best songs yet. You see, I saw the band before their first album was released, and I was impressed with the sheer energy and rock enthusiasm the youthful band was getting across. But then their full-length came out, and it sounded like the band was trying to re-hash something that had been done years ago...','http://www.adequacy.net/wp-content/uploads/images/covers/4255-Cover.jpg','http://www.adequacy.net/2000/08/paris-texas-brazilliant-ep/','2009-07-21T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - Brazilliant (from Splendid Magazine)','Brazilliant','It\'s hard not to wake up when listening to Brazilliant; it\'s fifteen minutes of punchy post-punk rock to power your morning commute. The Madison, WI band\'s first three tracks\nsound like the emo band they\'re supposed to be: a bit of Braid and some\nVersus whirled together.  \"Razor New Neighbors\" showcases Sam Vinz\'s\nmuscular drumming over the squealed lyrics of Scott Sherpe, and is easily the\nmost energetic song. Fans of FlinFlon would find the fretwork of \"400...','http://www.splendidezine.com/reviews/sep-11-00/paris.gif','http://www.splendidezine.com/reviews/sep-11-00/aag.html#11','2009-06-08T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - So, You Think It\'s Hot Here? (from Pitchfork)','','What is it with people trying to act British?  Seriously, what is this mysterious factor that\n    compels your average apple pie-eating, baseball-watching American male to assume a British\n    accent?  It can\'t be because a British air entails any sort of instant credibility on this side\n    of the Atlantic; just look at how long it took Blur to dump their \"ridiculously uncool\" status\n    in the U.S...','http://assets1.pitchforkmedia.com/images/original/14959.so-you-think-its-hot-here.gif','http://www.pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/20744-paris-texas-so-you-think-its-hot-here','2009-03-21T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - Like You Like An Arsonist (from Stylus Magazine)','','Whether Paris, Texas\' metamorphosis from melody-challenged emo unit to super charged pop rocket on Like You Like an Arsonist is a good thing or not is debatable. You might make the case that the band had finally begun to improve on its so-so approach by their third release, 2000\'s Brazilliant...','http://www.stylusmagazine.com/images/reviews/paris-texas-like-you-like-an-arsonist.jpg','http://www.stylusmagazine.com/reviews/paris-texas/like-you-like-an-arsonist.htm','2009-03-21T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - Silver (from Splendid Magazine)','Silver','This quaint little 7\" from Snapping Turtle came hot on the heels of the band\'s Polyvinyl debut.  So, you think it\'s hot here?  The A-side, \"Silver\", actually appears on that record and is a nice poppy post-punk guitar workout with an emo-like vocal flair.  But the real reason this slice of wax\ndeserves to be on your tuntable is its excellent B-side contribution \"My Week Beats Your Year\"...','http://www.splendidezine.com/reviews/apr-24-00/paris.gif','http://www.splendidezine.com/reviews/apr-24-00/aag.html#14','2008-10-28T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Like You Like an Arsonist - Paris, Texas','Like You Like an Arsonist ','Wisconsin rockers Paris, Texas may not know who they want to be musically on their sophomore long-player, Like You Like an Arsonist, but it doesn\'t stop them from dropping one hell of an album. Fusing an early Stone Temple Pilots assault to the quirky leanings of Hot Hot Heat on the undeniably catchy \"Bombs Away,\" the quintet manages to sound downright phenomenal when channeling the Foo Fighters on \"Action Fans Help Us...','','http://music.aol.com/album/like-you-like-an-arsonist/731695','2008-08-28T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas - Brazilliant! EP (from Pitchfork)','Brazilliant! EP',' ','http://assets1.pitchforkmedia.com/images/original/14960.brazilliant.gif','http://www.pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/20745-paris-texas-brazilliant-ep','2008-07-30T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('aol','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Madison, WI-based emo quintet Paris, Texas formed in late 1997; ...',true,'http://music.aol.com/artist/paris-texas/biography','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('myspace','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','paris texas has currently taken up residency in the city ...',true,'http://www.myspace.com/paristexasrock','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('wikipedia','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas is a punk rock band signed to New Line Records. They were formed at 112 S. Hancock, Madison, Wisconsin in December 1997 by their barefooted bassist, Matt Tennessen. \nAccording to CMJ New Music Magazine: \n\"Furious punk guitars that sound more rock than emo, backed by chaotic but somehow precise drumming...it\'s hard to believe Paris Texas were ever considered emo at all - there\'s much more bark than whine.\"',0,'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris%2C_Texas_(band)','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('ilike','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Paris, Texas was formed at 112 S. Hancock, Madison, WI ...',true,'http://www.ilike.com/artist/Paris,+Texas','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('last.fm','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','See also Paris Texas Paris, Texas started in 1997 as an energetic Madison, WI Punk/Indie/Rock band. They had three releases on Polyvinyl Record Company. After the amazing \"Brazilliant\" EP and corresponding tour in 2000, they broke up.   It seemed that it was the end; some said the break up was a ploy to get away from Polyvinyl, a rumor born from the fact that the band didn\'t play any Pre-Break PTX songs in their live shows.   Unreleased songs from Paris, Texas soon surfaced as the demo/EP \"Action Fans Help Us!\". The band reunited in 2003 and was signed to New Line Records releasing a final album \"Like You Like an Arsonist\", including re-recordings of songs from \"Action Fans Help Us!\" in 2004. Paris, Texas called it quits in 2005.  CMJ New Music Magazine said: \"Furious punk guitars that sound more rock than emo, backed by chaotic but somehow precise drumming...it\'s hard to believe Paris Texas were ever considered emo at all - there\'s much more bark than whine.\"',0,'http://www.last.fm/music/Paris%2C+Texas/+wiki','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('mog','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Madison, WI-based emo quintet Paris, Texas formed in late 1997; ...',true,'http://mog.com/artists/bio/mn163661/paris%20texas','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('facebook','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','We\'ve been a working band since 1971 and even before ...',true,'http://graph.facebook.com/129085777128007','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('rdio','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Madison, WI-based emo quintet Paris, Texas formed in late 1997; ...',true,'http://www.rdio.com/artist/Paris%2C_Texas/','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('itunes','ARDHWW41187B9A86B0','Madison, WI-based emo quintet Paris, Texas formed in late 1997; ...',true,'https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/paris-texas/id13533383','','