our next record.. We love stuff like Jellyfish and the Posies as well as Bowie, Queen the Beatles, the Kinks,etc which are our main reference points musically I suppose. lyrically stuff like HMHB, Sultans of Ping and <span>I, Ludicrous</span> are quite a big influences. What can we expect to see/hear from you in the future? I\'d like to hope we get asked to play more gigs so we\'re more of a live prospect. I\'ve mostly written our next album which is going to be called Colin\'s Godson 3D and mixed in 5:1 surround sound with','http://www.peenko.co.uk/2013/06/fresh-meat-monday-colins-godson.html','2013-06-10T00:00:00','2013-06-10T10:00:07');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('0f58a86c0d33a4ece8c1f129d9ddc0a0','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Wales Goes Pop – Gate Arts Centre, Cardiff 30th March','about\" probably deserves at least ten minutes of your time, I think. As their set progressed, their sound mellowed a bit but they were still most enjoyable. My daughter thought they rocked and who am I to disagree. Totem Terrors were a late substitution for The Proctors and the duo immediately made me think of <span>I, Ludicrous</span> albeit fleetingly. Their sparse sound of drum-machine and bass, with sparingly applied guitar for a bit of variety was excellent. Early Fall in places, with a bit of Oldham\'s Drink and Drive came to mind. Tip-top stuff throughout and I\'ll be getting a CD or two just as soon as I get the chance.','http://www.buzzinmusicblog.co.uk/wales-goes-pop-gate-arts-centre-cardiff-30th-march/5623','2013-04-03T00:00:00','2013-04-02T21:28:50');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('19c6af4b4e5f0d4750f9a9acba8dc5d4','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Live: Michael Clark Company, New Work 2012. Barbican Centre.','diligently working my way through the Rough Trade Records back catalogue. I\'d done Emiliana Torrini\'s Fisherman\'s Woman; done new things to Baxter Dury\'s Floor Show; delighted in Mazzy Star\'s She Hangs Brightly. Via Rough Trade Shops\' Indiepop 1 compilation I\'d even learned of the suitably barmy <span>I, Ludicrous</span>\' Preposterous Tales - a track I still shove on whenever I\'m feeling decidedly London, whatever that may mean. But Green Gartside was of immediate intrigue - a reclusive, self-deprecating creative meritorious of copious column inch operating at a time when the glutinous pages of the NME','http://www.dotsanddashes.co.uk/2012/10/live-michael-clark-company-new-work.html','2012-11-02T00:00:00','2012-10-26T16:53:29');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('079142270609ac9643380e0650945079','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Ouch, Baby. Ariel Pink\'s Haunted Graffiti, Mature Themes.','Rosenberg rubbing us up the wrong way from the off, and behaving like the petulant jerk he oft plays within the live arena. The choppy New Wave stylings of Is This The Best Spot? never hit the proverbial either, despite the puerile syllabics of \"G-spot\" and comes across as Adam Ant conspiring with <span>I, Ludicrous</span> on a throwback SNES soundtrack nobody wants nor needs. In keeping with Del Rey\'s loathed videogame vibe is the title track, another flimsy kicker flapping about in a dubious brand of soul. Thank fuck, therefore, for Only In My Dreams: an oneiric pop swoon to rival Can\'t Hear My Eyes, whether slapped on','http://www.dotsanddashes.co.uk/2012/08/ouch-baby-ariel-pinks-haunted-graffiti.html','2012-09-13T00:00:00','2012-08-20T15:32:28');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('9fa09a35742f40b82b943c72ccdbea8f','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Another Friday Night','\"It\'s true, man... everything I say is true...\" Clearly influenced by one Mark E. Smith, and with a fine fuzzy backing, this remains one of the best - and funniest - pop songs of 1987. Typically British, too. One for the road, ok? Alright then. <span>I, Ludicrous</span> - Preposterous Tales Another Friday Night','http://ramone666.blogspot.com/2012/07/another-friday-night.html','2012-09-24T00:00:00','2012-07-13T15:55:29');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('e4d04c58a83943055a4c2fc45694ed6f','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Chugging On. The Wedding Present, Valentina.','guitar octaves and drones of \"You\'re really way out of my league\". Speaking of leagues, were Meet Cute frantically writhing around over at Elland Road then the punk drudge of Back a Bit... Stop would unfortunately be scrapping it out in Sunday leagues in Gedge\'s native Bramley, coming across as <span>I, Ludicrous</span> having a stab at ska to prove irredeemably ludicrous in itself. Stranger still is The Girl from the DDR, as Gedge insistently affirms his adoration for a certain someone (again played by the contextually loveless le Moko) before ultimately concluding: \"I don\'t think I\'m ever gonna leave my girlfriend...','http://www.dotsanddashes.co.uk/2012/03/chugging-on-wedding-present-valentina.html','2012-03-28T00:00:00','2012-03-19T17:12:54');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('9f715e7ee0b2f9122ecc2e3239d49d12','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Reeling In The Years: 1987','by Matt Gaynor New Order - True Faith That Petrol Emotion - Big Decision It\'s Immaterial - Driving <span>Away</span> <span>From</span> <span>Home</span> Wedding Present - My Favourite Dress Soup Dragons - Soft As Your Face U2 - Running To Stand Still <span>I, Ludicrous</span> - Preposterous Tales Julian Cope - World Shut Your Mouth One Thousand Violins - Locked Out of the Love-In Colorblind James Experience - Considering A Move To Memphis Master list ... Reeling In The Years: 1987','http://sweepingthenation.blogspot.com/2011/02/reeling-in-years-1987.html','2011-04-02T00:00:00','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('2c6441fa901201dedefc6af37be3b2e2','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','We\'ll support you ever more','Top-notch pop news ahoy. The legendary <span>I, Ludicrous</span> have only gone and released a brand new download single. We\'re The Support Band (a new recording of an old favourite) is available from itunes and all the usual online suspects. Here\'s the <span>FAB</span> promo video! ... We\'ll support you ever more','http://toomuchapplepie.blogspot.com/2009/10/well-support-you-ever-more.html','2009-11-04T00:00:00','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('88651f01535f8b7b22ba67485a152ed5','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','More Peelie','post to listen to audio] » The Fall – Theme From Sparta FC [See post to listen to audio] » The Fall – Kicker <span>Conspiracy</span> » Kicker <span>Conspiracy</span> video (filmed at Burnley) Oh and how about Mark E. Smith reading out the football results: » Link to video » Find more Peel via the tag: http://www.footballandmusic.co.uk/tag/johnpeel/ » Also keeping it Peel is Dandelion Radio who are having a \"Peel Legends\" month featuring bands who have featured on Peel Sessions including <span>I, Ludicrous</span> amongst ... More Peelie','http://www.footballandmusic.co.uk/more-peelie/','2009-10-29T00:00:00','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('860815b610710e4bd1afa12d0d01d76b','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Frankosonic','Frankosonic Frankosonic The Frankie Machine MP3 Blog of Choice Wednesday, December 24, 2008 Reggae Christmas Quick song for christmas. If this doesn\'t get you feeling festive then NOTHING will. <span>Eek-A-Mouse</span> - Christmas A Come Particularly like the lyrics around the 40-50 second mark subscribe to frankosonic posted by Francis @ 7:59 PM   0 comments Wednesday, December 10, 2008 <span>I, Ludicrous</span> Peel Session Unsurprisingly another Peel Session request fulfillment post..this time for Steve at Teenage ... Frankosonic','http://www.duckworthsquare.com/frankosonic/frankosonic/index.html','2009-02-27T00:00:00','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('dd6fad00a333b951473423831be3c23d','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','I, Ludicrous Peel Session','Unsurprisingly another Peel Session request fulfillment post..this time for Steve at Teenage Kicks It\'s the one and only Peel Session that <span>I, Ludicrous</span> recorded - 21 fun filled years ago.. Since their classic debut flexi release \"Preposterous Tales\" the band have continued to record albums & gig sporadically, in fact I saw them for the first time supporting The Fall in Sheffield earlier this year and they were, indeed, fabulous The two highlights of this session for me are \"Quite Extraordinary\" - the tribute to ex-BBC sports commentator and \"A Question Of Sport\" host David Coleman (who I have ... not) and \"A Pop Fan\'s Dream (Sunday Lunch With The Geldofs)\" wherein the narrator wins a competition to have a meal with Bob Geldof, his lovely wife Paula (Yates - now she IS dead) and their daughter Fifi Trixibelle (Peaches and Pixie weren\'t even born at this point). A story told with such a perfect level of sincerity that you can\'t quite tell how serious they are being until the final line delivers the pay-off. The band had an excellent new EP out this year called \"Dirty Washing\" which I heartily recommend and you can buy it from their website <span>I, Ludicrous</span> - Peel Session 1987 <span>I, Ludicrous</span> Peel Session','http://www.duckworthsquare.com/frankosonic/frankosonic/2008/12/i-ludicrous-peel-session.html','2012-11-02T00:00:00','2008-12-10T15:55:25');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('6804e7d88b5670e552bd93fed3eb3857','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Marc Riley Sessions: The Wedding Present & Toquiwa','Valentina album, \'Heather\' from 1991\'s Seamonsters and \'You Should Always Keep In Touch With Your Friends\', from their 1988 compilation of early material Tommy. Toquiwa, currently supporting the Weddoes, also came in to play a cover their tourmates\' \'Kennedy\' - have a listen below: Next week, we\'ll be posting a session from BEAK>, while Mark has <span>I, Ludicrous</span> on Monday, Magic Arm on Tuesday and Vic Godard And The Sexual Objects on Thursday Marc\'s show is on every Monday to Thursday from 7pm-9pm, and you can tune in on DAB or via the 6 Music website here. Marc Riley Sessions: The Wedding Present & Toquiwa','http://thequietus.com/articles/10788-marc-riley-6-music-sessions-the-wedding-present','2012-11-23T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('0f4a410361220bf1215f35d685d34487','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Marc Riley Sessions: Wild Billy Childish','Wild Billy Childish And The Spartan Dreggs were in session for Marc\'s November 15 show, continuing their Hellenic trawl with three songs from two of their three albums this year: \'Headlong Fly The Achaeans\' and \'We Spartan Dreggs (Be Fine)\' from Dreggredation and \'The Sir John Hawkins Memorial Car Park\' from Tablets Of Linear B - have a listen below: BEAK> are in session tonight, with pop trio <span>I, Ludicrous</span> following next Monday, November 26. Marc\'s show is on every Monday to Thursday from 7pm-9pm, and you can tune in on DAB or via the 6 Music website here. Marc Riley Sessions: Wild Billy Childish','http://thequietus.com/articles/10738-marc-riley-6-music-sessions-wild-billy-childish','2012-11-21T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENNews (ENNews.news_id,ENNews.artist_id,ENNews.name,ENNews.summary,ENNews.url,ENNews.date_found) VALUES ('1f15a20f0b1698c77fe16f96d7e7a892','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Old music: Serious Drinking - Love on the Terraces','a fair wind and a push from John Peel they might find themselves an audience - I remember seeing Terry & Gerry playing skiffle to 4,000 people on a bill at the Hammersmith Odeon. Other groups dedicated themselves to making their audience laugh: Half Man Half Biscuit have endured, as have <span>I, Ludicrous</span> on an even smaller scale. One of the having-a-laugh scenes was based in Norwich, where the Higsons, the Farmers Boys and Serious Drinking emerged from the University of East Anglia. In one clip from an early 80s TV show, one of the Norwich musicians expresses his astonishment that anyone\'s taking any notice,','http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/feb/27/old-music-serious-drinking-love-terraces','2012-02-27T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('myspace','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','\"NO ONE SHOULD DIE BEFORE HEARING THIS LEGENDARY OUTFIT\" - ...',true,'http://www.myspace.com/iludicrous','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('aol','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','Emerging from South London in 1987, the comedy duo of ...',true,'http://music.aol.com/artist/i-ludicrous/biography','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('wikipedia','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','This article needs additional citations for verification. Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. (October 2010)  \n I, Ludicrous is a three-piece pop music ensemble, formed in South London in 1985, by John Procter (born 1957) and David Rippingale (\"Will Hung\") (b. 1956). The band sprang to notoriety at the end of 1987, when their debut flexi release (\"Preposterous Tales\") reached Number 11 in John Peel\'s Festive Fifty. \nI, Ludicrous are still producing music today, and play occasional live dates, primarily in London. In January 2008 (Martin Brett) from Voice of the Beehive joined the band on bass guitar.',0,'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I,_Ludicrous','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('last.fm','ARKCMYJ1187FB5619C','I, Ludicrous is a two piece popular music ensemble formed in london in 1985 by John Procter (b. 1957) and David Rippingale (\"Will Hung\") (b. 1956).  The band sprang to notoriety at the end of 1987 when their debut flexi release (\'Preposterous Tales\') reached Number 11 in John Peel\'s Festive Fifty.  I, Ludicrous are still producing music today and play occasional live dates, primarily in London.  I, Ludicrous at MusicBrainz.',0,'http://www.last.fm/music/I%2C+Ludicrous/+wiki','','