inly be my preferred choice, I can\'t help but be a bit ecstatic about the amount of material released all within the same period, especially after ... <span>Ring, Cicada</span> remained mostly dormant for an extended period of time. Anyway, I certainly ... \"Instrumental\" track on their MySpace dozens of times before the release of the album and the rest of the tracks that I hadn\'t heard before stand up just as well. Heroes of the <span>Kingdom</span> appear to be more of a traditional rock band for Powell, in that the music is not heavily instrumental like in <span>Ring, Cicada</span> and puts Powell\'s vocals to work far more. They end up fitting quite nicely with what the band is doing, especially on some ... of the slower numbers that are definitely cool to hear. HOTK is a lot less jammy too, and like most Midwestern influenced rock it has an added focus melodically. While HOTK','http://www.builtonaweakspot.com/2009/05/heroes-of-kingdom-hotk.html','2009-08-19T00:00:00','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBlogs (ENBlogs.blog_id,ENBlogs.artist_id,ENBlogs.name,ENBlogs.summary,ENBlogs.url,ENBlogs.date_found,ENBlogs.date_posted) VALUES ('b5787bac4276965605f6ae58b9e56f4c','ARLS45Z1187B994763','Built on a Weak Spot: Black Ladies - Naked Caveman 7\'\'','\'s Aftermath Monthly Mix: January 2009 Gravel - As For Tomorrow 7\'\' (1992, Estrus) Screen Vinyl Image - Interceptors Shelflife - Shelflife <span>Picasso</span> <span>Trigger</span> - Plutonium 7\'\' (1992, Jettison) Crawlpappy - Temple Body 7\'\' (1991, Blackout!) Vandal X - All Lined Up Against the Wall Best of 2009 Zu - Carboniferous Cacaw - Get a Brain SPC-ECO - 3D <span>Ring, Cicada</span> - History\'s End   ... Built on a Weak Spot: Black Ladies - Naked Caveman 7\'\'','http://www.builtonaweakspot.com/2009/02/black-ladies-naked-caveman-7.html','2009-03-21T00:00:00','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARLS45Z1187B994763','Ring, Cicada - Self-titled EP (from Lost At Sea)','Self-titled EP','More.  In so many ways I listen to this self-titled EP by Ring, Cicada and think to myself: More. With a total run time of 12 minutes 21 seconds, I\'m left wanting to hear more. I want more music, more songs. While I\'m content to press repeat on the CD player, I\'d much rather press repeat after having heard twice as many songs. At least having seen them live I can say that there is more to be heard.  Ring, Cicada are an instrumental rock outfit. Heavy on the rock...','http://www.lostatsea.net/LAS/archives/reviews/records/ringcicada_selftitled.jpg','http://www.lostatsea.net/review.phtml?id=60763568341fe7a5c4a8ca','2010-02-19T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARLS45Z1187B994763','Ring, Cicada - Good Morning, Mr. Good (from Lost At Sea)','Good Morning, Mr. Good','After one too-short, highly acclaimed release, Ring, Cicada made their mark with those who were lucky enough to find them. Here, they work with Steve Albini to force a full-fledged album on the world, reaching (and damaging) every ear in their path. It works well for this post-Don Caballero St. Louis quartet that Mr. Big Black/Shellac himself is at the helm, for they are as deserving of his status as he is of their promise...','http://www.lostatsea.net/LAS/archives/reviews/records/ringcicada_goodmorningmrgood.jpg','http://www.lostatsea.net/review.phtml?id=152013652641fe79dc6ee1b','2010-02-19T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARLS45Z1187B994763','Ring, Cicada - Good Morning, Mr. Good (from Delusions of Adequacy)','Good Morning, Mr. Good','Ring, Cicada\'s story isn\'t an entirely new one - Midwestern rock outfit stomps around for a couple of years, garners press and acclaim off of a few EPs and a blistering live show, ends up in some Chicago studio with Steve Albini behind the knobs. Yes, Albini - that twisted, undersized scene-maker - seems to find his way onto every record with guitars these days, fighting the same fight since Big Black emerged in the 80s...','http://www.adequacy.net/wp-content/uploads/images/covers/2926-Cover.jpg','http://www.adequacy.net/2003/05/ring-cicada-good-morning-mr-good/','2009-07-21T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARLS45Z1187B994763','Ring, Cicada - Ring, Cicada','Ring, Cicada ','An outstanding first release from this instrumental band from Illinois. Gorgeously intricate meshes of melodic guitar and moving rhythms forming dreamy textures of limitless imagination. At times like a simpler, more orderly version of Don Caballero, mixed with touches of Hum and Sonic Youth minus the vocals. Beautiful homemade artwork on the packaging adds a touch of sentimentality to the overall effect of the album.','','http://music.aol.com/album/ring-cicada/455689','2008-08-28T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARLS45Z1187B994763','Good Morning Mr. Good - Ring, Cicada','Good Morning Mr. Good ','Ring, Cicada returns after a collection of EPs for their first official full-length, Good Morning Mr. Good; this time with occasional vocals from Christian Powell that sound like a mellowed Black Francis. The music remains driving and progressive, like math rock with a little less of a metal bent, as the band charges through spiky but emotive numbers like \"Esoterrorism.\" At times as dark and relentless as .....','','http://music.aol.com/album/good-morning-mr-good/584896','2008-08-28T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENReviews (ENReviews.artist_id,ENReviews.name,ENReviews.release,ENReviews.summary,ENReviews.image_url,ENReviews.url,ENReviews.date_found) VALUES ('ARLS45Z1187B994763','Review of Ring, Cicada - Cicada: Good Morning, Mr. Good. (from Splendid Magazine)','Cicada: Good Morning, Mr. Good.','Less talk, more rock -- that ludicrous AOR radio positioning statement seems to embody this St. Louis-based band\'s musical state of mind. With a strong emphasis on the creation and dispersion of complex post-rock instrumentals, Ring, Cicada boggles minds with heavy guitars, odd time signatures and sharp tempo changes. While a few tracks on Good Morning, Mr. Good feature vocals, the band prefers to follow the familiar path of angular Midwestern instrumental rock...','http://www.splendidezine.com/reviews/jun-23-03/ring.gif','http://www.splendidezine.com/review.html?reviewid=3264256757418235','2008-07-30T00:00:00');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('myspace','ARLS45Z1187B994763','We are a ROCK BAND! WE ROCK!..Ring, Cicada is a ...',true,'http://www.myspace.com/ringcicada','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENBiographies (ENBiographies.site,ENBiographies.artist_id,ENBiographies.desc,ENBiographies.truncated,ENBiographies.url,ENBiographies.licence_attribution,ENBiographies.licence_attribution_url,ENBiographies.licence_type,ENBiographies.licence_url,ENBiographies.licence_version) VALUES ('last.fm','ARLS45Z1187B994763','Hailing from Collinsville, Illinois, math-rockers Ring, Cicada went through a number of line-up changes and three now out-of-print EPs before releasing their debut full-length, Good Morning Mr. Good, on 54º40\' or Fight! in April of 2003. This album marked the debut of guitarist Christian Powell as a vocalist on three songs, which was a change of pace for the once-instrumental group. This was the group\'s second stint with vocals, following a brief period when former drummer Chris Carl (later of Cheerleader) rejoined the group as its frontman.  In 2009 Ring, Cicada released their second LP, History\'s End, in mp3 only, but plans for an eventual vinyl pressing still exist.   Powell also plays guitar and sings in Heroes of the Kingdom. Former bassist Eric Abert now plays in The Life and Times.   Guitarist Dave Goodman currently plays in Dibiase and bass in Ashes and Iron.',0,'http://www.last.fm/music/Ring%2C+Cicada/+wiki','','','','','');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENTerms (ENTerms.name,ENTerms.artist_id,ENTerms.frequency,ENTerms.weight) VALUES ('rock','ARLS45Z1187B994763',1,1);INSERT IGNORE INTO ENTerms (ENTerms.name,ENTerms.artist_id,ENTerms.frequency,ENTerms.weight) VALUES ('math rock','ARLS45Z1187B994763',0.21104985878332813,0.7269503546099291);INSERT IGNORE INTO ENTerms (ENTerms.name,ENTerms.artist_id,ENTerms.frequency,ENTerms.weight) VALUES ('alternative pop rock','ARLS45Z1187B994763',0.0679458581590142,0.2801418439716312);INSERT IGNORE INTO ENTerms (ENTerms.name,ENTerms.artist_id,ENTerms.frequency,ENTerms.weight) VALUES ('indie rock','ARLS45Z1187B994763',0.09730107090346271,0.2127659574468085);INSERT IGNORE INTO ENTerms (ENTerms.name,ENTerms.artist_id,ENTerms.frequency,ENTerms.weight) VALUES ('instrumental','ARLS45Z1187B994763',0.07584239782557053,0.13120567375886524);INSERT IGNORE INTO ENUrls (ENUrls.site,ENUrls.artist_id,ENUrls.url) VALUES ('official','ARLS45Z1187B994763','http://www.ringcicadarock.com');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENUrls (ENUrls.site,ENUrls.artist_id,ENUrls.url) VALUES ('lastfm','ARLS45Z1187B994763','http://www.last.fm/music/Ring%2C+Cicada');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENUrls (ENUrls.site,ENUrls.artist_id,ENUrls.url) VALUES ('mb','ARLS45Z1187B994763','http://musicbrainz.org/artist/5b5d700a-2741-4638-bf18-8e1f9bace16a.html');INSERT IGNORE INTO ENUrls (ENUrls.site,ENUrls.arti